# Title: Custom Social Media Hosts Block List
#
# This hosts file is a custom block list specifically for social media domains.
# It blocks domains associated with popular social media platforms.
#
# Date: 12 April 2025 16:30:00 (UTC)
# Number of unique domains: 38
#
# To use this file:
# 1. Save it as social_media_hosts.txt.
# 2. Host it on a web server or place it locally where Pi-hole can reference it.
# 3. In the Pi-hole Admin Interface, go to Group Management > Adlists (or Settings > Blocklists)
#    and add the URL or file path to this block list.
# 4. Run "pihole -g" to update gravity.
#
